# Primitive::Keyless::Hash::SHA2::Specification

## Module Parameters

Module parameters configure compile-time specialization for this module (for example widths and initial constants).

| Name | Kind | Signature | Notes |
|------|------|-----------|-------|
| `w` | Type Parameter | `#` | Length of words, in bits, that are used during hashing. |
| `DigestSize` | Type Parameter | `#` | Length of the message digest produced by the hash algorithm. |
| `H0` | Value Parameter | `[8][w]` | Initial hash value. |

### Parameter Constraints

<details><summary>Constraint 1: `w` is a multiple of `32`, and `w` is at least `32`, and `w` is at most `64`.</summary>

Formal constraint: `(w % 32 == 0, 32 <= w, 64 >= w)`

</details>

<details><summary>Constraint 2: `8 * w` is greater than or equal to `DigestSize`, and `DigestSize` is a multiple of `8`.</summary>

Formal constraint: `(8 * w >= DigestSize, DigestSize % 8 == 0)`

</details>

